# Cursor Rules for StemPay Lottery Manager

## Code Style Rules

### Comments
- **NO COMMENTS** - Make code descriptive and self-documenting instead of using comments
- **Exception**: Only a single descriptive comment is allowed on the first line of any file in the `contracts/` folder
- Remove all existing comments from code files
- Use descriptive variable names, function names, and clear logic flow instead of comments

### Code Quality
- Write self-documenting code with clear, descriptive names
- Use meaningful variable and function names that explain their purpose
- Structure code logically to make it easy to understand without comments
- Prefer explicit code over commented explanations

### File Organization
- Keep contracts folder clean with only essential first-line comments
- Remove all inline comments, block comments, and documentation comments
- Focus on writing code that speaks for itself through good naming and structure
